<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="59" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="59">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="59">
In this study larvae was found living on marginal rocks of a low order stream and in isolated rocky seepages, extending the altitudinal records up to 2700 m a.s.l. Environmental characterization: Water temperature varied from 10-22 °C; dissolved oxygen 6.4-9.0 mg.l-1; pH 5.0-6.0; very slow water flow; vegetal coverage completely absent (shrub-herbaceous vegetation). 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. pepinellii" pageId="18" pageNumber="59" rank="species" species="pepinellii">P. pepinellii</taxonomicName>
was found in PARNASO (Rio de Janeiro State) and APASM (Minas Gerais State). Low altitudinal specificity (IndVal: 0.25; p = 0.32).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
